Under the authority of the French Ambassador to the Republic of Ivory Coast, the defence attaché is the local representative of the French Ministry of the Armed Forces, he is appointed by the French Minister of the Armed Forces and, in this capacity, ensures the representation of the various authorities of the ministry (DGRIS, DCSD, EMA, DRM, DGA) in the Republic of Ivory Coast. 

Thus, the defence attaché is the head of the cooperation, security and defense mission. He is also, within the diplomatic post, the advisor and head of department of the French Ambassador for defense issues. The cooperation, security and defense mission contributes in the Republic of Côte d'Ivoire to the preservation, development and promotion of French interests in the field of security and defense, both with the Ivorian authorities and with the representations of third countries or international and non-governmental organizations acting locally. 

In general, it covers the three main areas of a bilateral defense relationship which are : 

- exchanges in defense policy ;
- technical military cooperation ; 
- relations in arms fields ; 

In fact, the cooperation, security and defense mission is the engine of Franco-Ivorian structural cooperation, especially through support for the ENVRs (National School with Regional Vocation) present in Ivory Coast : the AILCT (International Academy for counter-terrorism), the ISMI (Interregional Maritime Security Institute) and the AMSIC (Military Academy of Information and Communications Systems).

The Air Operations CoE, a multi-national manned French-funded organization, draws on experience and skills within air operations, technical simulation and Air C2 systems domains to provide English-speaking training and expertise.

AO CoE personnel includes highly-trained resident officers from the French Air Force, Army and Navy, as well as from Greece, Italy, Swiss and the United States, in order to give a diverse, joint air operations perspective to all AO CoE activities.

Our expertise covers the four transformation pillars:
• Education and Training;
• Analysis and Lessons Learned;
• Concept Development and Experimentation;
• Doctrine Development and Standards.

Alguns objetivos da Liga são: 
- Colocar os estudantes da PUC Goiás em contato com os conhecimentos em torno da Segurança Internacional e Defesa e seus campos de atuação, promovendo a intersecção do aprendizado teórico com a prática; 
- Aprimorar o conhecimento e a formação universitária dos membros da LAESID por meio de debates, leituras, palestras e outras atividades de caráter político, cultural, científico e social; 
- Buscar a aproximação entre os corpos discente e docente da PUC Goiás com outras instituições de ensino superior; e 
- Desenvolver trabalhos científicos, promover cursos, congressos, encontros, entre outras atividades em grupos que contem com a participação de alunos, professores e profissionais, buscando os objetivos propostos pela LAESID.

Наша студентська організація діє в рамках Українського католицького університету. Разом із нашими студентами ми гуртуємо спільноту УКУ задля допомоги війську.

У нас діють 5 напрямків волонтерської роботи:
1) Дія (координація проектів, налагодження партнерських відносин та створення нових контактів для розвитку організації);
2) Збори (організація зборів, координація учасників, створення ефективних процесів);
3) Вишколи (організація та проведення тренінгів, що підвищують військову готовність та свідомість);
4) Пам'ять (просування культури пам'яті, особливо про тих, хто загинув із спільноти УКУ);
5) Комунікація (висвітлення подій, організованих спільнотою, та поширення інформації про них у соціальних мережах).
